{"nodes": [{"id": "2026_06_05_runtime_help_docs_spec_drift_guard_design_document", "label": "Design", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-runtime-help-docs-spec-drift-guard/design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_05_runtime_help_docs_spec_drift_guard_design_context", "label": "Context", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-runtime-help-docs-spec-drift-guard/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "pi-vimmode already has finite semantic action metadata, protected shortcut diagnostics, Ex command-line parsing, transient info/error messages, feature/settings docs, and durable OpenSpec specs. Existing runtime diagnostics answer customization questions through `:vimdoctor`, `:keymap`, `:mapcheck`, and `:actions`, but they do not answer broader questions such as \"what feature areas exist?\", \"what limits apply?\", or \"what was the last runtime message?\". Docs/spec/runtime drift is a known failure"}, {"id": "2026_06_05_runtime_help_docs_spec_drift_guard_design_goals_non_goals", "label": "Goals / Non-Goals", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-runtime-help-docs-spec-drift-guard/design.md", "source_location": "line 7", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Goals:** - Provide compact runtime help through finite read-only Ex commands: `:help [topic]`, `:features [query]`, and `:messages`."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_runtime_help_docs_spec_drift_guard_design_decisions", "label": "Decisions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-runtime-help-docs-spec-drift-guard/design.md", "source_location": "line 26", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "### 1. Add a pure runtime help/feature registry seam Target seams: new `src/runtime-help.ts` or equivalent, `src/customization.ts`, `src/config.ts`, `src/ex.ts`, and tests."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_runtime_help_docs_spec_drift_guard_design_1_add_a_pure_runtime_help_feature_registry_seam", "label": "1. Add a pure runtime help/feature registry seam", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-runtime-help-docs-spec-drift-guard/design.md", "source_location": "line 28", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: new `src/runtime-help.ts` or equivalent, `src/customization.ts`, `src/config.ts`, `src/ex.ts`, and tests. Create a typed registry for runtime help entries. Each entry should include a stable id, category, aliases/topics, compact summary, examples, limits, related runtime commands/actions, docs anchor, spec anchor, and test anchor when applicable. The registry may import or accept existing customization/action metadata so keymap, protected shortcut, macro, mark, search, and transfor"}, {"id": "2026_06_05_runtime_help_docs_spec_drift_guard_design_2_keep_help_features_and_messages_finite_ex_diagnostics", "label": "2. Keep :help, :features, and :messages finite Ex diagnostics", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-runtime-help-docs-spec-drift-guard/design.md", "source_location": "line 42", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/ex.ts`, `src/modal/engine.ts`, `src/modal/types.ts`, `src/modal/view.ts`, and tests. Extend the finite Ex parser with exact command names `help`, `features`, and `messages`. `:help` and `:features` accept an optional bounded query/topic string. `:messages` accepts no arguments in v1. Unsupported abbreviations and unexpected trailing syntax return existing Ex error messages rather than implying Vimscript grammar."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_runtime_help_docs_spec_drift_guard_design_3_implement_messages_as_capped_message_introspection_not_a_pager", "label": "3. Implement :messages as capped message introspection, not a pager", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-runtime-help-docs-spec-drift-guard/design.md", "source_location": "line 57", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/modal/types.ts`, `src/modal/engine.ts`, `src/modal/view.ts`, `src/vim-editor.ts`, and tests. Store a bounded recent message log in modal/editor state, capped to a small constant such as 20 entries. Log user-facing transient messages from Ex success/error/info and optional no-op feedback. Do not log active Ex input. `:messages` reads the log and shows a width-safe one-row summary such as count plus latest message; the `:messages` output itself should not be appended to the log."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_runtime_help_docs_spec_drift_guard_design_4_make_docs_drift_guard_structural_and_narrow", "label": "4. Make docs drift guard structural and narrow", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-runtime-help-docs-spec-drift-guard/design.md", "source_location": "line 71", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: new test/helper under `test/` or `scripts/`, `docs/features.md`, `docs/settings.md`, `openspec/specs/*`, and `package.json` only if a named script is warranted. Add guard checks that run in the normal validation path, preferably `bun test`. The guard should compare structured data, not infer semantics from prose. Recommended checks:"}, {"id": "2026_06_05_runtime_help_docs_spec_drift_guard_design_5_preserve_existing_customization_diagnostics_contracts", "label": "5. Preserve existing customization diagnostics contracts", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-runtime-help-docs-spec-drift-guard/design.md", "source_location": "line 90", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/customization.ts`, `src/ex.ts`, `src/modal/engine.ts`, and `openspec/specs/vim-customization-diagnostics/spec.md`. `:`actions remains action-focused and finite. `:features` may reuse action entries but should explain broader feature areas, limits, docs anchors, and effective enablement when runtime options disable marks, macros, search highlighting, prompt structures, or prompt transforms. `:mapcheck`, `:keymap`, and `:vimdoctor` behavior should not change except for shared me"}, {"id": "2026_06_05_runtime_help_docs_spec_drift_guard_design_risks_trade_offs", "label": "Risks / Trade-offs", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-runtime-help-docs-spec-drift-guard/design.md", "source_location": "line 103", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "- Registry drift from source constants \u2192 import/reuse `src/customization.ts` and config defaults where possible; add coverage tests for command/action/settings anchors. - Docs guard too brittle \u2192 validate structured anchors and explicit banned contradictions first; avoid broad prose parsing. - `:messages` increases modal state complexity \u2192 cap history, keep one-row summary, and add focused clearing/history tests."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_runtime_help_docs_spec_drift_guard_design_migration_plan", "label": "Migration Plan", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-runtime-help-docs-spec-drift-guard/design.md", "source_location": "line 112", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "1. Add pure runtime help/feature registry and unit tests without changing runtime behavior. 2. Add docs drift guard tests against current docs/source and fix any existing mismatches. 3. Extend Ex parser with `help`, `features`, and `messages` parse results."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_runtime_help_docs_spec_drift_guard_design_ref_src_customization_ts", "label": "customization.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-runtime-help-docs-spec-drift-guard/design.md", "source_location": "line 13", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_05_runtime_help_docs_spec_drift_guard_design_ref_src_types_ts", "label": "types.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-runtime-help-docs-spec-drift-guard/design.md", "source_location": "line 23", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_05_runtime_help_docs_spec_drift_guard_design_ref_src_config_ts", "label": "config.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-runtime-help-docs-spec-drift-guard/design.md", "source_location": "line 23", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_05_runtime_help_docs_spec_drift_guard_design_ref_src_runtime_help_ts", "label": "runtime-help.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-runtime-help-docs-spec-drift-guard/design.md", "source_location": "line 30", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}], "edges": [{"source": "2026_06_05_runtime_help_docs_spec_drift_guard_design_document", "target": "2026_06_05_runtime_help_docs_spec_drift_guard_design_context", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-runtime-help-docs-spec-drift-guard/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "2026_06_05_runtime_help_docs_spec_drift_guard_design_document", "target": "2026_06_05_runtime_help_docs_spec_drift_guard_design_goals_non_goals", "relation": "references", "confid